body:
Hello,
I have class with some default `parameter type` and cannot override it, which should be legal.

The code:

```verilog
module test;
  typedef enum {
    FOO_0,
    FOO_1
  } foo_e;

  typedef enum {
    BAR_0,
    BAR_1
  } bar_e;

  class baz #(parameter type E = foo_e);
    static function void print();
      E enum_item = enum_item.first();
      do begin
        $display("%s", enum_item.name());
        enum_item = enum_item.next();
      end while (enum_item != enum_item.first());
    endfunction
  endclass

  initial begin
    baz#(bar_e)::print();
    $finish;
  end
endmodule
```

Output (`foo_e` was not overridden with `bar_e`):
